The wall of the tubes is thin, comprising an irregular meshwork of triactines, tetractines and a few tripods (
Fig. 9B
), which are located only on external tubes. Projecting into the interior of the tubes are the apical actines of the tetractines.

The size of the triactines and tetractines is uniform. The actines of the triactines are conical or cylindrical, while the tetractines are always conical. They are straight, with a blunt tip. The apical actine of the tetractines (
Fig. 9C
) is conical, sharp, straight and thinner and shorter than the facial ones. In the distal part, before the tip of the actine, there are sharp spines arranged in 3-4 rows. These spines are directed toward the tip of the actine. Some apical actines, particularly those of young spicules, have only vestigial spines.
